The '''Icelandic Student Loan Fund''' (Icelandic: ''Lánasjóður íslenskra námsmanna'' or ''LÍN'') is a government-funded and government-run [[student loan]] fund for Icelandic citizens. It provides loans for living expenses of up to 7 years of university studies. Repayment of the loans is at below-market-rate [[interest]], with a two-year [[grace period]] upon completion of studies.<ref name=student-loan>{{cite web|title=Student loan|url=http://student.is/student_loan|publisher=student.is|accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref><ref name=ed-ac>{{cite web|title=Icelandic Loans|url=http://www.ed.ac.uk/schools-departments/student-funding/financial-support/student-loans/icelandic|publisher=ed.ac.uk|accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref><ref name=loans>{{cite web|title=The Icelandic Student Loan Fund|url=http://english.hi.is/icelandic_student_loan_fund/icelandic_student_loan_fund|publisher=english.hi.is|accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref><ref name=books-google>{{cite book|title=OECD Economic Surveys: Iceland 2006|url=https://books.google.com.np/books?id=f2kvs9P5y_oC&pg=PA109&lpg=PA109&dq=Icelandic+Student+Loan+Fund&source=bl&ots=jc0OUbKpIt&sig=rR_7V6M_suMC5Xd-z-Gpwp_IFHY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=g3s1U_W7GYTGrAeboIDoCw&ved=0CFoQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=Icelandic%20Student%20Loan%20Fund&f=false|publisher=books.google.com.np|accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref>
