{{Infobox book | name = Seen Art? | title_orig = | translator = | image = seenart.jpg | author = [[Jon Scieszka]], [[Lane Smith (illustrator)|Lane Smith]] | cover_artist = [[Lane Smith (illustrator)|Lane Smith]] | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = | genre = [[children's book]] | publisher = [[Viking Press]] | release_date = 1995 | media_type = | pages = 48 | size_weight = | isbn = 978-0-670-05986-7 | dewey = [E] 22 | congress = N7477 .S36 2005 | oclc = 60348593 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} {{Portal |Children's literature}}
'''''Seen Art?''''' is a [[children's book|children's]] [[picture book]] written by [[Jon Scieszka]] and illustrated by [[Lane Smith (illustrator)|Lane Smith]]. It was published in 1995 by [[Viking Press]], and is aimed at a reading age of 4 to 8.
It depicts a child's view of the art collection at the [[Museum of Modern Art]] in [[New York City]] via a storyline that follows a young boy's quest for his friend called Art. Asking people whether they have seen Art, and where Art is, leads him on a journey around the Museum. At the end of the book he finds his friend waiting for him outside the Museum.<ref name="Amazon">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Seen-Art-Jon-Scieszka/dp/0670059862/|title=Seen Art? (Hardcover)|work=amazon.com|accessdate=2009-01-29}}</ref>
The book has been published in Spanish translation as ''En Busca de Arte''.<ref name="Spanish">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Busca-Arte-Seen-Art-Spanish/dp/8478716432/|title=En Busca de Arte / Seen Art (Spanish Edition) (Hardcover)|work=amazon.com|accessdate=2009-01-29}}</ref>
